Code and data for SVM clustering in the sense of JÃ¤ger, List & Sofroniev 2017
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------


REQUIREMENTS

- python 2.7
- numpy 1.13.3
- pandas 0.17.1
- python-igraph 0.7.1
- lingpy 2.6.2
- biopython 1.66
- scipy 1.0.0
- sklearn 0.17.0


WORKFLOW

> cd code
> python2.7 svmClustering.py [dataset].tsv


The program expects the data file in data/, and it writes the result into results/.
The result file extends the input file by two columns, containing the SVM- and LexStat
cognate classes.
